Helping people live better----**PAGE 28**# Declaring the OutbreakThe OMT will meet to review management of the outbreak – what was handled well and what could be improved in managing future outbreaks and review/analyze the following once the outbreak is declared over:- Number of ill residents;
- Number of deceased residents during the outbreak;
- Number of hospitalized residents;
- Number of ill staff;
- Number of areas in the home affected;
- Pattern of spread;
- Total number of days in outbreak;
- Effectiveness of control measures;
- Audits of staff compliance with routine practices and additional precautions;
- Residents’ ability to follow control measures;
- Challenges with community visitation; and
- Additional costs associated with the outbreak.> **To declare an outbreak over, the LTCH must not have had any new cases of infection in either residents or staff, which meet the case definition for the period of time established by the OMT i.e., predetermined decision rules that the OMT has decided to use to declare the outbreak over.

